Log In:
It will prompt you for a username, enter it.
It will prompt you for a password, enter it.
If these credentials exist in the systemUsers file, the main function will load depending if you are a standard or admin user.

Standard User:
1. View Properties - Prints a list of properties in the propertyList file.
2. Logout - Logs the user out of the system.

Admin User:
1. View Properties - Prints a list of properties in the propertyList file.
2. Add Properties - Prompts you for inputs for the property, which it will compile and add to the propertyList file.
3. Edit Properties - Prompts you to select a property then for a new value for each value, then update the propertyList file.
4. Delete Properties - Prompts you to select a property then removes the selected property from the propertyList file.
5. Search Properties - Prompts you for a specific value to search for, then will print any and all relevant property listings in the propertyList file.
6. Logout - Will save any and all changes made to the propertyList file, then log the user out.
